iew process. It requires authors, peer reviewers, and editors to protect sensitive information, including manuscript details and AI-generated content, from unauthorized access or disclosure. AI technology must be used in a way that upholds confidentiality, especially when handling unpublished materials. Journals like Emerald and De Gruyter Brill emphasize the importance of confidentiality in the use of AI tools, highlighting the risks of data breaches and intellectual property misuse. [records: Entities (23), Relationships (113, 40, 344, 346, 343)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"AI Technology has a restricted but evolving role in peer review\",\n            \"explanation\": \"AI technology is subject to strict regulations in the peer review process. While some journals prohibit its use entirely, others permit limited applications, such as language improvement or detecting AI-generated content, provided that usage is disclosed. Peer reviewers are generally prohibited from using AI tools during evaluations but may use them for final report preparation if they declare such use. However, AI cannot replace human judgment, and its integration into the peer review process remains a topic of ongoing debate. [records: Entities (41, 13), Relationships (41, 13, 177, 180, 392)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Peer Reviewers have significant ethical and procedural responsibilities\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Peer reviewers play a vital role in the peer review process, with responsibilities including maintaining confidentiality, avoiding the misuse of manuscript content, and adhering to AI policies. They are prohibited from using AI to complete reviews but may use it for language assistance, provided they disclose this. Peer reviewers must also ensure that AI tools do not compromise the integrity of the review process, and they are accountable for the accuracy and views expressed in their reports. [records: Entities (9, 180, 181, 